---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import List from '../components/List.astro';
import Swiper from '../components/Swiper.astro';
---

<Layout title="Powers & Abilities">

	<section class="container">

		<article>
			<h2>Water Manipulation</h2>
			<p>Wields the sea as both weapon and shield. He can whip waves into blades, shape whirlpools beneath enemy ships, or pull moisture from the air to form mist and illusions.</p>
			<div class="ability-details">
				<h3>Combat Applications:</h3>
				<List items={[
					"Whip waves into razor-sharp blades",
					"Create devastating whirlpools beneath enemy vessels", 
					"Pull moisture from air to form concealing mist",
					"Shape water into protective barriers",
					"Generate illusions using water vapor"
				]} />
				<p><strong>When enraged:</strong> His control expands into the very tide â€” entire harbors rise and fall to his command.</p>
			</div>

			<Swiper 
				slides={
					[
						{
							src: '../src/assets/ability-water-blades.jpg',
							alt: 'Abyss forming a blade of water from the sea',
							caption: 'Water Blade'
						},
						{
							src: '../src/assets/ability-water-kick.jpg',
							alt: 'Abyss forming a water whip as he kicks',
							caption: 'Water Whip'
						},
						{
							src: '../src/assets/ability-water-tentacles.jpg',
							alt: 'Abyss surrounded by water tentacles',
							caption: 'Water Tentacles'
						},
						{
							src: '../src/assets/ability-ice-spear.jpeg',
							alt: 'Abyss creating an ice spear from water',
							caption: 'Ice Spear'
						}
					]
				}
			/>

		</article>

		<article>
			<h2>Abyssal Summon</h2>
			<p>Calls forth creatures from the deepest trenches of the ocean, beings that exist between life and death in the crushing darkness below.</p>
			<div class="ability-details">
				<h3>Summoned Entities:</h3>
				<List items={[
					"Translucent leviathans from the deep trenches",
					"Skeletal mariners - the souls of drowned sailors",
					"The Kraken - ancient terror of the depths",
					"Schools of spectral sea creatures",
					"Ghostly remnants of sunken ships and their crews"
				]} />
				<p><strong>Note:</strong> These beings serve only as long as they remain connected to water.</p>
			</div>
		</article>

		<article>
			<h2>Rebirth of the Tide</h2>
			<p>The ultimate gift of the ocean - true immortality bound to the endless cycle of tides and waves.</p>
			<div class="ability-details">
				<h3>Regenerative Powers:</h3>
				<List items={[
					"Mortal wounds heal through ocean's power",
					"Can regenerate lost limbs using seawater",
					"Immunity to drowning and water-based attacks",
					"Resistance to conventional weapons",
					"Body reforms from water when destroyed"
				]} />
				<p><strong>Immortal Covenant:</strong> He cannot die so long as the sea endures.</p>
			</div>
		</article>

		<article>
			<h2>Limitations & Weaknesses</h2>
			<p>Even the herald of the deep is not without bounds...</p>
			<List items={[
				"Powers diminish when far from large bodies of water",
				"Extreme heat can weaken water-based abilities",
				"Sacred or magical weapons may cause serious harm",
				"Bound to the ocean's will - not entirely his own master"
			]} />
		</article>

	</section>

</Layout>